Reasoning: This paper focuses on analyzing the fault-proneness of coding rules proposed by SonarQube, which is a tool used for software quality analysis and management. This falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The study involves analyzing the coding rules and their impact on inducing bugs, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD). The use of machine learning models for fault prediction also falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
